simplified boolean expressions using "== false" and "!= true".
simplified boolean expressions: removed "== true" and "!= false".

support extracting textures in the TX_START/TX_END namespace.

The textures are saved into the "tx_start" directory, and
remembered in wadinfo.txt in the [TX_START] section.

Lumps which are detected to be PNG or JPEG images are saved
as-is (no conversion is done), otherwise we assume they are
DOOM patch format and attempt to convert them to a real image
format (just like graphics, patches, etc are handled).

support composing wads with textures in TX_START/TX_END namespace.

This feature is activated by a [TX_START] section in the info
file, and reads image files from the "tx_start" directory.

Entries are generally converted to DOOM patch format, but using
a positive integer after the texture name will copy the file
directly into the wad (no conversion), useful for PNG images
which most ports support (ZDoom supports several more formats).
